HEADWORD: chaetognath
<hw>chaetognath</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>any worm of the Chaetognatha;
transparent marine worm with horizontal lateral and caudal fins and a
row of movable curved spines at each side of the mouth.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> arrowworm.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

